cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

The paper deals with 3D object reconstruction from a single image, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves estimating 2.5D sketches and 3D object shape, which involves graphics (cs.GR). The approach is learning-based, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is end-to-end trainable and can be applied to real images, which involves robotics (cs.RO).
